['---\n'
 ' Documentation/iio/adxl313.rst | 196 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n'
 ' Documentation/iio/index.rst   |   1 +\n'
 ' 2 files changed, 197 insertions(+)\n'
 ' create mode 100644 Documentation/iio/adxl313.rst\n'
 '\n'
 'diff --git a/Documentation/iio/adxl313.rst b/Documentation/iio/adxl313.rst\n'
 'new file mode 100644\n'
 'index 000000000000..8c4e2d141594\n'
 '--- /dev/null\n'
 '+++ b/Documentation/iio/adxl313.rst\n'
 '@@ -0,0 +1,196 @@\n'
 '+.. SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0\n'
 '+\n'
 '+===============\n'
 '+ADXL313 driver\n'
 '+===============\n'
 '+\n'
 "+This driver supports Analog Device's ADXL313 on SPI/I2C bus.\n"
 '+\n'
 '+1. Supported devices\n'
 '+====================\n'
 '+\n'
 '+* `ADXL313 <https://www.analog.com/ADXL313>`_\n'
 '+\n'
 '+The ADXL313is a low noise density, low power, 3-axis accelerometer with\n'
 '+selectable measurement ranges. The ADXL313 supports the ±0.5 g, ±1 g, ±2 g '
 'and\n'
 '+±4 g ranges.\n'
 '+\n'
 '+2. Device attributes\n'
 '+====================\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Accelerometer measurements are always provided.\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Temperature data are also provided. This data can be used to monitor the\n'
 '+internal system temperature or to improve the temperature stability of the\n'
 '+device via calibration.\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Each IIO device, has a device folder under '
 '``/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:deviceX``,\n'
 '+where X is the IIO index of the device. Under these folders reside a set '
 'of\n'
 '+device files, depending on the characteristics and features of the '
 'hardware\n'
 '+device in questions. These files are consistently generalized and '
 'documented in\n'
 '+the IIO ABI documentation.\n'
 '+\n'
 '+The following tables show the adxl313 related device files, found in the\n'
 '+specific device folder path ``/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:deviceX``.\n'
 '+\n'
 '++---------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| 3-Axis Accelerometer related device files         | '
 'Description                                              |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| in_accel_scale                                    | Scale for the '
 'accelerometer channels.                    |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| in_accel_x_calibbias                              | Calibration offset '
 'for the X-axis accelerometer channel. |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| in_accel_x_raw                                    | Raw X-axis '
 'accelerometer channel value.                  |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| in_accel_y_calibbias                              | y-axis acceleration '
 'offset correction                    |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| in_accel_y_raw                                    | Raw Y-axis '
 'accelerometer channel value.                  |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| in_accel_z_calibbias                              | Calibration offset '
 'for the Z-axis accelerometer channel. |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| in_accel_z_raw                                    | Raw Z-axis '
 'accelerometer channel value.                  |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+\n'
 '++---------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| Miscellaneous device files            | '
 'Description                                  |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| name                                  | Name of the IIO '
 'device.                      |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| in_accel_sampling_frequency           | Currently selected sample '
 'rate.              |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+| in_accel_sampling_frequency_available | Available sampling frequency '
 'configurations. |\n'
 '++---------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Channels processed values\n'
 '+-------------------------\n'
 '+\n'
 '+A channel value can be read from its _raw attribute. The value returned is '
 'the\n'
 '+raw value as reported by the devices. To get the processed value of the '
 'channel,\n'
 '+apply the following formula:\n'
 '+\n'
 '+.. code-block:: bash\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        processed value = (_raw + _offset) * _scale\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Where _offset and _scale are device attributes. If no _offset attribute is\n'
 '+present, simply assume its value is 0.\n'
 '+\n'
 '+The ADXL313 driver offers data for a single types of channels, the table '
 'below\n'
 '+shows the measurement units for the processed value, which are defined by '
 'the\n'
 '+IIO framework:\n'
 '+\n'
 '++-------------------------------------+---------------------------+\n'
 '+| Channel type                        | Measurement unit          |\n'
 '++-------------------------------------+---------------------------+\n'
 '+| Acceleration on X, Y, and Z axis    | Meters per Second squared |\n'
 '++-------------------------------------+---------------------------+\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Usage examples\n'
 '+--------------\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Show device name:\n'
 '+\n'
 '+.. code-block:: bash\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> cat name\n'
 '+        adxl313\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Show accelerometer channels value:\n'
 '+\n'
 '+.. code-block:: bash\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> cat in_accel_x_raw\n'
 '+        2\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> cat in_accel_y_raw\n'
 '+        -57\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> cat in_accel_z_raw\n'
 '+        2\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> cat in_accel_scale\n'
 '+        0.009576806\n'
 '+\n'
 '+- X-axis acceleration = in_accel_x_raw * in_accel_scale = 0.0191536 m/s^2\n'
 '+- Y-axis acceleration = in_accel_y_raw * in_accel_scale = -0.5458779 m/s^2\n'
 '+- Z-axis acceleration = in_accel_z_raw * in_accel_scale = 0.0191536 m/s^2\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Set calibration offset for accelerometer channels. Note, the calibration '
 'will be\n'
 '+rounded according to the graduation of LSB units:\n'
 '+\n'
 '+.. code-block:: bash\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> cat in_accel_x_calibbias\n'
 '+        0\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> echo 50 > '
 'in_accel_x_calibbias\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> cat in_accel_x_calibbias\n'
 '+        48\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Set sampling frequency:\n'
 '+\n'
 '+.. code-block:: bash\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> cat '
 'in_accel_sampling_frequency\n'
 '+        100.000000\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> cat '
 'in_accel_sampling_frequency_available\n'
 '+        6.250000 12.500000 25.000000 50.000000 100.000000 200.000000 '
 '400.000000 800.000000 1600.000000 3200.000000\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> echo 400 > '
 'in_accel_sampling_frequency\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> cat '
 'in_accel_sampling_frequency\n'
 '+        400.000000\n'
 '+\n'
 '+3. Device buffers\n'
 '+=================\n'
 '+\n'
 '+This driver supports IIO buffers.\n'
 '+\n'
 '+All devices support retrieving the raw acceleration measurements using '
 'buffers.\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Usage examples\n'
 '+--------------\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Select channels for buffer read:\n'
 '+\n'
 '+.. code-block:: bash\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> echo 1 > '
 'scan_elements/in_accel_x_en\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> echo 1 > '
 'scan_elements/in_accel_y_en\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> echo 1 > '
 'scan_elements/in_accel_z_en\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Set the number of samples to be stored in the buffer:\n'
 '+\n'
 '+.. code-block:: bash\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> echo 10 > buffer/length\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Enable buffer readings:\n'
 '+\n'
 '+.. code-block:: bash\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> echo 1 > buffer/enable\n'
 '+\n'
 '+Obtain buffered data:\n'
 '+\n'
 '+.. code-block:: bash\n'
 '+\n'
 '+        root:/sys/bus/iio/devices/iio:device0> hexdump -C '
 '/dev/iio\\:device0\n'
 '+        ...\n'
 '+        000000d0  01 fc 31 00 c7 ff 03 fc  31 00 c7 ff 04 fc 33 00  '
 '|..1.....1.....3.|\n'
 '+        000000e0  c8 ff 03 fc 32 00 c5 ff  ff fc 32 00 c7 ff 0a fc  '
 '|....2.....2.....|\n'
 '+        000000f0  30 00 c8 ff 06 fc 33 00  c7 ff 01 fc 2f 00 c8 ff  '
 '|0.....3...../...|\n'
 '+        00000100  02 fc 32 00 c6 ff 04 fc  33 00 c8 ff 05 fc 33 00  '
 '|..2.....3.....3.|\n'
 '+        00000110  ca ff 02 fc 31 00 c7 ff  02 fc 30 00 c9 ff 09 fc  '
 '|....1.....0.....|\n'
 '+        00000120  35 00 c9 ff 08 fc 35 00  c8 ff 02 fc 31 00 c5 ff  '
 '|5.....5.....1...|\n'
 '+        00000130  03 fc 32 00 c7 ff 04 fc  32 00 c7 ff 02 fc 31 00  '
 '|..2.....2.....1.|\n'
 '+        00000140  c7 ff 08 fc 30 00 c7 ff  02 fc 32 00 c5 ff ff fc  '
 '|....0.....2.....|\n'
 '+        00000150  31 00 c5 ff 04 fc 31 00  c8 ff 03 fc 32 00 c8 ff  '
 '|1.....1.....2...|\n'
 '+        00000160  01 fc 31 00 c7 ff 05 fc  31 00 c3 ff 04 fc 31 00  '
 '|..1.....1.....1.|\n'
 '+        00000170  c5 ff 04 fc 30 00 c7 ff  03 fc 31 00 c9 ff 03 fc  '
 '|....0.....1.....|\n'
 '+        ...\n'
 '+\n'
 '+See ``Documentation/iio/iio_devbuf.rst`` for more information about how '
 'buffered\n'
 '+data is structured.\n'
 '+\n'
 '+4. IIO Interfacing Tools\n'
 '+========================\n'
 '+\n'
 '+See ``Documentation/iio/iio_tools.rst`` for the description of the '
 'available IIO\n'
 '+interfacing tools.\n'
 'diff --git a/Documentation/iio/index.rst b/Documentation/iio/index.rst\n'
 'index 2d6afc5a8ed5..c106402a91f7 100644\n'
 '--- a/Documentation/iio/index.rst\n'
 '+++ b/Documentation/iio/index.rst\n'
 '@@ -31,6 +31,7 @@ Industrial I/O Kernel Drivers\n'
